    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>Alex Haley (Alexander Murray Palmer Haley),
         African-American author and journalist (August 11,
         1921--February 10, 1992), author of Roots: The Saga of an
         American Family (1976). This accession consists of nineteen
         items, 1961 &amp; 1963 and n.d., chiefly typescript
         manuscripts and research notes for "Dark Secret's Last Race: A
         Drama In Real Life." It profiles champion thoroughbred
         racehorse Dark Secret and his final victory at the 1934 Jockey
         Club Gold Cup race despite a broken leg. Also present is
         research material concerning his trainer James Edward "Sunny
         Jim" Fitzsimmons (b. 1874).</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>Arranged alphabetically by subject</p>
    </arrangement>
    <descgrp type="add">
